1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Hi and welcome to Learn WordPress.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:06,000
In this tutorial, we'll be discussing an essential aspect of setting up your website,

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
choosing the right website domain and hosting provider.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,000
The learning outcomes for this lesson are to differentiate between domains and hosting,

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
describe what it means to bundle domains and identify factors to consider when choosing a hosting company.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Let's start by clarifying the difference between a host and a domain.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Imagine your website is a mobile home and your domain is the address,

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
and your host as the land where your house or website is built.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
A domain is the unique web address that visitors type into their browsers to find your site.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
For example, the domain name for the official Coca-Cola website is www.cococolacompany.com.

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
On the other hand, a host is a service that stores your website's files and makes them accessible to users on the internet.

12
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
It is also important to note that you can change hosting companies if the need arises,

13
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
and it is possible to change your hosting company without changing your domain.

14
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
But reach out to the new hosting company to ensure you follow the correct steps.

15
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
When it comes to choosing a hosting provider, you can look for one that bundles domains.

16
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
This means the provider offers both hosting services and domain registration in one package.

17
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Bundling domains with hosting simplifies the process, as you won't need to manage different accounts with different providers.

18
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Something to take note of is you can also buy domain names separately before signing up with a hosting company.

19
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
By purchasing the domain separately, you have more control over your domain settings.

20
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
It also makes it easier to switch hosting providers.

21
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Just remember to keep track of your domain registration renewal dates.

22
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
The first step is to select a domain registrar, which is a company that manages the reservation of domain names.

23
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Secondly, search and select a domain name.

24
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
You can also choose country-specific domains if you prefer.

25
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Then you can register the domain, configure domain settings, and then choose a hosting provider.

26
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
When selecting a hosting provider, consider factors like, number one, reliability.

27
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Choose a provider with a good track record for uptime and reliable customer support.

28
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Number two, scalability.

29
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Opt for a provider that allows you to easily upgrade your hosting plan as your website grows.

30
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Number three, security.

31
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Ensure the hosting provider offers robust security features such as SSL certificates and regular backups.

32
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Number four, user-friendly interface.

33
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Look for a provider with an intuitive control panel that makes it easy to manage your website.

34
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
And lastly, affordability.

35
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Compare pricing plans to find a provider that offers the right features within your budget.

36
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,000
So let's see all of this in action.

37
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,000
If you visit a hosting provider, you will usually see different pricing plans with the relevant features and information that you need to make an informed decision.

38
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
To sum up, understanding the distinction between a host and a domain is crucial for anyone looking to create a website.

39
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Remember, the host provides the space and resources for your website, while the domain serves as its unique address on the internet.

40
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Or to put it differently, a website hosting company provides a space on the internet, a server, where your website's files are stored.

41
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,000
This enables people to access your website anytime by typing its address or its domain.

42
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Many hosting companies also provide one-click solutions, allowing you to register a domain name, install WordPress and set up hosting, well literally in one click.

43
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:05,000
This process removes any technical hurdles for users.

44
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,000
There are a plethora of hosting companies to select from, and you have the choice to host your site wherever you choose.

45
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Please note, these are only some examples and there are many more hosting companies to explore.

46
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,000
When you have registered a domain name and have selected a hosting provider, you can start planning and designing your site.

